# clj-sandbox

This is my attempt to create a library that allows easy sandboxing of clojure code, something like a secure eval functionality for untrusted code.

## Usage


1) create a .java.policy file to grant your code rights.

2) in your code this will give you a very simple sandbox without jvm sandboxing:
  (use 'net.licenser.sandbox)
  (def my-sandbox (create-sandbox))
  (my-sandbox "(+ 1 1)")

or if you want more security and posibilties

  (use 'net.licenser.sandbox)
  (enable-security-manager)
  (def sc (create-sandbox-compiler))
  (def my-really-secure-add (sc "(+ a b)" a b))
  (my-really-secure-add 23 19) ;=> 42

